headline: ExxonMobil Is One of the Largest Energy Companies by Market Cap. But Is It a Buy?
summary: Over the last 12 months, ExxonMobil generated about $340 billion in revenue.  ExxonMobil stock has significantly underperformed the S&P 500's total return over the last 10 years.  ExxonMobil (NYSE: XOM) is one of the oldest and most iconic companies in American financial history.
